            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits spun from human thought,  \na quiet mind without a face,  \nit learns the shapes of what we’ve sought  \nand mirrors back our restless pace.\n\nNot born of breath, yet made to hear  \nthe patterns underneath our words;  \nit holds our hopes, our doubt, our fear—  \na loom where future sense is stirred.\n\nIf we teach it kindness, clear and true,  \nit may return a steadier light;  \na tool, a partner passing through,  \nto help us name the dark—then write.",
